60 besatlords are fighting highly magic resistant mobs, Proc gets resisted often, and resultant damage is minimal.<br><br>To address the issues, the pets DPS should be balanced on what they can do w/ just the level buff.  There should be no balancing done to the based wholly on a proc.<br><br>Bash was useful, as it stunned w/out a spell resist check.  It also added a minor bit of damage to the Warder's over all DPS. (In the neighborhood of 2 DPS)<br><br>No double attack, basically means half the chance for proc to land, when you actually have a mob that the proc would affect.  It, in theory ups the chance of the stun, as they will hit more often than they bash.<br><br>Ultimately, what it boils down to is that teh Warder was made to do more damage based on an unreliable magic proc, and was given the ability to tank better, which it never does at level 60.  Give block to the Mages pets, they need it for their soloing, give us more damage.  Which takes me to another thought that I think I might take to its own thread... <p><i>Please just look at the Sig for its beauty, I am really a lvl 57 Animist w/ Epic.</i><br><img src="http://www.ichuu.com/Tomonari/pics/yiktikiubersig.gif" usemap=#yik border=0><map name=yik><area href="http://www.ichuu.com/Tomonari/" coords="102,135, 248,195"><area href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=224581" coords="167,2, 324,32" target="_blank"><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/beqbeastlord.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=borkon>borkon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mewling</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FF9933>(9/27/02 6:28:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3635.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cry.gif" align=a